01:12:22,440 --> 01:12:26,319
He used to make the tip of the bomb,
the thing that finds, uh...

1081
01:12:26,440 --> 01:12:28,908
New York or Washington, you know?

1082
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:32,310
- Ooh.
- Check your hoses.
We got some thermal variation.

1083
01:12:32,440 --> 01:12:35,796
Stamper, let's look at the couplings
back on the shuttle.

1084
01:12:37,280 --> 01:12:40,078
Okay. Shut down. Uh--

1085
01:12:46,680 --> 01:12:49,592
- Guys!
- Hold on a second.
- What's that noise?

1086
01:12:51,640 --> 01:12:54,393
Oh, no! God!

1087
01:12:56,840 --> 01:13:00,469
- What is it?
- Leak! Leak! Leak!

1088
01:13:02,400 --> 01:13:06,359
Get your men
back to the shuttle! Go!

1089
01:13:06,440 --> 01:13:09,557
Go on! Hurry up!
Get out of there!

1090
01:13:09,640 --> 01:13:11,676
Now there's really sparks!

1091
01:13:11,760 --> 01:13:15,639
- Pull lever!
- This is the lever!

1092
01:13:15,720 --> 01:13:19,349
- Colonel, we must get him out of there!
- A.J., come on out!

1093
01:13:22,720 --> 01:13:25,075
Hurry! Hurry!

1094
01:13:27,040 --> 01:13:29,270
Emergency! Break away!

1095
01:13:29,400 --> 01:13:32,153
We got a fire
in the fuel pod!

1096
01:13:34,560 --> 01:13:38,394
- Come on!
- Come on! Get in here!
A.J.'s stuck in the fuel pod!

1097
01:13:40,440 --> 01:13:43,989
- We're losing it!
- Come on out of there!

1098
01:13:53,360 --> 01:13:57,194
Control, this is lndependence.
l am seeing vibration--

1099
01:13:58,640 --> 01:14:01,473
- Malloy, talk to me!
- Not good. We got sparks
and fire in the fuel pod.

1100
01:14:01,600 --> 01:14:05,434
- lndependence, blow those locks
and get outta there now!
- Dump the hoses now! We're going!

1101
01:14:05,560 --> 01:14:09,439
- What happened?
Let me shut off the O2 feed!
- Harry, it's burnin' up!

1102
01:14:09,520 --> 01:14:13,798
Damn! Max, Rock, get in here! Get down
there and crack these pipes over here!

1103
01:14:13,920 --> 01:14:17,754
- Harry, no! lt's burnin' up!
- We're goin' back for the other team!

1104
01:14:17,840 --> 01:14:21,150
Switch on the personnel locators.

1105
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:23,157
Trackin' A.J. He's climbin'.

1106
01:14:23,240 --> 01:14:25,515
- No!
- Go! Go!

1107
01:14:25,640 --> 01:14:29,918
lt's too late! Get back to the shuttle!
This thing's gonna blow!

1108
01:14:30,040 --> 01:14:31,598
No!

1109
01:14:31,720 --> 01:14:36,794
Colonel, we gotta move now!
Come on! You're gonna die!

1110
01:14:36,920 --> 01:14:39,514
- Wait a minute! Wait a minute!
We got a man in there!
- Open that door and we'll all die!

1111
01:14:39,640 --> 01:14:42,234
- Fuel leak!
- Get out of there!

1112
01:14:44,040 --> 01:14:46,508
Evac now! Let's go! Let's go!

1113
01:14:48,480 --> 01:14:51,995
Come on back!
No, wait! The door is broken!

1114
01:14:53,360 --> 01:14:56,193
- No!
- They got the fire
sealed in the fuel pod.

1115
01:14:56,320 --> 01:14:58,311
- They locked it down.
- Tracking 'em back to the shuttle.

1116
01:14:58,440 --> 01:15:01,477
They've still got two men
trapped in there!

1117
01:15:01,600 --> 01:15:05,832
Keep running! The shuttle's another
75 feet! Where's the rest of the team?

1118
01:15:05,960 --> 01:15:09,157
- Let's get out of here! The pod--
- Wait, wait, wait! Where's A.J.?
- A.J.'s gone!

1119
01:15:09,280 --> 01:15:14,229
- We're not leavin' without A.J.!
- He's gone! lt's too late!

1120
01:15:14,320 --> 01:15:16,788
Come on!
This way is our only chance!

1121
01:15:16,880 --> 01:15:19,235
So it's minus 100!

1122
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:22,397
Very cold. Hold breath,
or lung freezes!

1123
01:15:27,760 --> 01:15:31,594
Get back to the shuttle!
And lock that door!

1124
01:15:31,720 --> 01:15:35,633
- Come on!
- Hurry, A.J.!
- Leave him alone! Leave him alone!

1125
01:15:35,720 --> 01:15:38,598
- l tried! l tried. But A.J.--
- lt's on fire! lt's on fire, Harry!

1126
01:15:38,720 --> 01:15:41,154
- lt's them or all of us!
- lt's on fire!

1127
01:15:41,280 --> 01:15:43,794
- Full thrust.
- We're gonna get hit.

1128
01:15:59,240 --> 01:16:03,552
Lev! Lev, the door's gonna blow!

1129
01:16:03,680 --> 01:16:05,591
No!

1130
01:16:08,720 --> 01:16:12,235
We're going! lt's gonna blow!

1131
01:16:12,360 --> 01:16:15,989
- A.J.'s still in there!
- Blow the locks. No, the bolts!

1132
01:16:16,120 --> 01:16:20,272
- We've gotta blow--
- l think we're almost there!

1133
01:16:21,440 --> 01:16:24,113
Flight, lndependence
does not have A.J. They're gonna
close the door without him.

1134
01:16:24,200 --> 01:16:27,272
- Tracking. They're 75 feet
from the shuttle.
- Just tell them to air lock
the door and go!

1135
01:16:27,400 --> 01:16:29,755
- Dog the hatch now!
- Close it!

1136
01:16:35,040 --> 01:16:36,951
Ho--

1137
01:16:37,040 --> 01:16:41,511
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Colonel! That thing's
comin' right for us! We got to move!

1138
01:16:45,240 --> 01:16:48,232
Hurry up!
There's the shuttle door!

1139
01:16:49,320 --> 01:16:52,676
Fire's coming at us!
Close the door now!

1140
01:16:56,720 --> 01:16:58,870
Go! Go! Go!

1141
01:17:05,760 --> 01:17:09,992
Freedom, the lndependence crew
is on board and accounted for.

1142
01:17:10,120 --> 01:17:14,079
- We're even heavy one cosmonaut.
- They got 90% of their fuel.

1143
01:17:14,760 --> 01:17:19,515
-Pretty intense, huh?
-That's why l told you, ''Touch nothing.''

1144
01:17:19,640 --> 01:17:21,471
But you're bunch of cowboys.

1145
01:17:25,680 --> 01:17:28,114
So while the consciousness
of the planet is unified...

1146
01:17:28,200 --> 01:17:31,954
focused on the NASA mission taking place
right now in the vast ocean of space...

1147
01:17:32,040 --> 01:17:34,634
we're now in the final hours
of the mission...

1148
01:17:34,760 --> 01:17:37,877
as the Freedom and lndependence
prepare to slingshot around the moon.

1149
01:17:46,120 --> 01:17:51,478
Morning, guys. lt's time to suit up,
l guess. Uh, we got a big day.

1150
01:17:51,560 --> 01:17:55,189
- Eighteen seconds to radio interrupt.
- Booster sequence confirmed.

1151
01:17:55,280 --> 01:17:58,238
This is Houston.
Roger that, Freedom. We copy.

1152
01:17:58,320 --> 01:18:02,677
- Shuttles are ready
for the burn around the moon.
- Radio contact terminated. We're out.

1153
01:18:04,040 --> 01:18:07,237
Nine and a half Gs for 11 minutes.
l'd start praying about right now.

1154
01:18:13,160 --> 01:18:17,199
So this is the part where we're supposed
to just hold on real tight and, uh,
hope we don't die.

1155
01:18:17,320 --> 01:18:20,790
- Stand by for lunar roll.
- High inclination. Lunar orbit.

1156
01:18:23,000 --> 01:18:25,468
You boys got those wills
filled out correctly?

1157
01:18:40,840 --> 01:18:44,037
All right, men, this is what
we trained for. Now just suck it up!

1158
01:18:44,160 --> 01:18:46,435
On the mark. Five, four...

1159
01:18:46,560 --> 01:18:49,028
three, two, one.

1160
01:18:59,120 --> 01:19:01,953
- ls this supposed to be like this?
- Don't worry. This is normal.

1161
01:19:02,080 --> 01:19:05,356
- How would you know?
- 14,000 miles an hour.

1162
01:19:05,480 --> 01:19:08,074
- Four Gs.
- How long does this last?

1163
01:19:08,200 --> 01:19:10,031
Six Gs.

1164
01:19:12,040 --> 01:19:14,952
- 15,000.
- Really heavy, man!
- This isn't normal.

1165
01:19:15,080 --> 01:19:18,072
- What do you mean, ''this isn't normal''?
- This is way worse!

1166
01:19:18,160 --> 01:19:21,357
- Eight Gs. Hang tight!
- l'm not gonna make it!

1167
01:19:21,480 --> 01:19:23,994
Oh, we're gonna die!

1168
01:19:24,120 --> 01:19:26,270
Twelve minutes.
Flight, we still got nothin' here.

1169
01:19:28,040 --> 01:19:30,031
This is too fast!

1170
01:19:34,160 --> 01:19:36,310
Ten Gs!

1171
01:19:47,720 --> 01:19:52,475
We're maxed at 22,500!

1172
01:20:01,000 --> 01:20:04,356
We have acquisition of signal
from lndependence and Freedom.

1173
01:20:04,480 --> 01:20:07,278
We're in, guys.
All right. Welcome back, team.

1174
01:20:07,400 --> 01:20:09,550
We have visual
of the target, Houston.

1175
01:20:18,280 --> 01:20:20,510
You see that?

1176
01:20:24,600 --> 01:20:26,670
Wow.

1177
01:20:28,560 --> 01:20:31,916
- Come in, lndependence.
- Houston, you gotta see this
to believe it.

1178
01:20:34,920 --> 01:20:38,276
Okay, team, let's take 'em in. Okay,
Quincy, how much tail debris do we have?

1179
01:20:38,400 --> 01:20:40,436
Freedom, turn on your FOD radar.

1180
01:20:40,520 --> 01:20:42,988
FOD radar on.

1181
01:20:44,120 --> 01:20:47,556
Everybody, hang on. This could get
a little rough. Engaging evasive radar.

1182
01:20:55,400 --> 01:20:57,277
Hold on!

1183
01:21:07,640 --> 01:21:09,232
Goddam! We got debris!

1184
01:21:11,200 --> 01:21:12,997
We're dumping auxiliary boosters.

1185
01:21:26,320 --> 01:21:28,788
- Houston, do you read me?
- We got debris!

1186
01:21:31,560 --> 01:21:34,313
- We're goin' in!
- We're comin' in hot!

1187
01:21:37,320 --> 01:21:39,959
lndependence, try to maintain
your present heading.
You've got a target L.Z.

1188
01:21:40,040 --> 01:21:43,032
- There's too much debris!
We gotta peel off!
- Negative!

1189
01:21:46,600 --> 01:21:48,431
We're hit!

1190
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:53,313
- Mayday, mayday!
- l've lost main thrusters.
Get 'em back up!

1191
01:21:53,440 --> 01:21:55,670
Mayday, Houston, mayday!
We've lost R.C.S. thrusters!

1192
01:21:55,800 --> 01:21:59,475
Mayday, Freedom, mayday! We are
out of control! We are going down!

1193
01:21:59,560 --> 01:22:01,994
Do you read me?
Freedom, we are going down!

1194
01:22:14,600 --> 01:22:16,670
We're gonna hit!

1195
01:22:25,680 --> 01:22:30,071
Everybody, go to your own life support!
Lock yourself in the cargo bay!

1196
01:22:31,960 --> 01:22:36,795
We are going down! Houston! Houston,
we are going down! We have lost control!

1197
01:22:36,880 --> 01:22:38,950
l can't get it on!

1198
01:22:40,320 --> 01:22:43,517
- Good luck, Freedom.
- Oh, my God, this is it.

1199
01:22:52,040 --> 01:22:54,190
No! No!

1200
01:22:59,800 --> 01:23:03,475
Pull it! Pull it! Go!

1201
01:23:32,400 --> 01:23:35,472
Sharp, what the hell is that?
ls that the lndependence?

1202
01:23:40,200 --> 01:23:43,556
Houston, lndependence is a dead stick.
They're not gonna make it.

1203
01:23:55,960 --> 01:23:58,349
Houston, lndependence has gone down.

1204
01:24:09,880 --> 01:24:12,189
When l touch this baby down,
full reverse thrust.

1205
01:24:12,320 --> 01:24:15,232
- Fires on your right, Sharp!
- Reversing the thrusters!

1206
01:24:16,320 --> 01:24:18,754
Hang tight! Hang tight!

1207
01:24:18,880 --> 01:24:24,193
- Houston, we overshot our landing field
We overshot our landing field.
- Oh, no!

1208
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:45,875
God!

1209
01:25:00,520 --> 01:25:04,149
lnitiate system light system check. Make
sure we can still get off this rock.

1210
01:25:04,280 --> 01:25:07,716
Our electrical system is screwed.
l'm going to back-up. Fuel seals check.

1211
01:25:07,840 --> 01:25:11,674
- Engine seals check.
Pressure seals check.
- Oh, God. Oh!

1212
01:25:13,960 --> 01:25:15,871
Anyone hurt?

1213
01:25:17,320 --> 01:25:22,838
Where's-- Where's the other shuttle?
What happened to the other shuttle?

1214
01:25:22,920 --> 01:25:25,912
- lndependence is off the grid.
- ''Off the grid''?

1215
01:25:26,000 --> 01:25:29,356
What are you, a freakin' cyborg?
What does that mean?

1216
01:25:29,480 --> 01:25:33,155
Hey, you saw it yourself, right?
They're gone.

1217
01:25:34,600 --> 01:25:38,115
Come in, Freedom. This is
CAPCOM Houston. Freedom, come in.

1218
01:25:38,240 --> 01:25:41,915
This is CAPCOM Houston.
Come in, Freedom.

1219
01:25:42,040 --> 01:25:44,838
- God!
- Let's just ask God
to take care of our friends.

1220
01:25:46,800 --> 01:25:48,870
May they rest in peace.

1221
01:25:50,560 --> 01:25:52,755
Amen.

1222
01:25:59,080 --> 01:26:01,799
We got eight hours.

1223
01:26:01,920 --> 01:26:05,117
Let's get this job done
and go home.

1224
01:26:05,240 --> 01:26:09,233
Nothin'. Come on, Watts,
Sharp, somebody.

1225
01:26:09,320 --> 01:26:12,039
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1226
01:26:12,160 --> 01:26:17,678
Come in, Freedom. Freedom, come in.
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1227
01:26:17,800 --> 01:26:19,995
- Maybe you shouldn't be here.
- Come in, Freedom.

1228
01:26:20,120 --> 01:26:24,033
- l don't have anywhere else to go.
- Freedom, come in.
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1229
01:26:26,120 --> 01:26:28,793
All right, let's get the tools unpacked
and fire up the Armadillo.

1230
01:26:28,880 --> 01:26:31,872
- We're not getting a damn thing
on the inertial nav system.
- l know where we are.

1231
01:26:32,000 --> 01:26:34,878
Please step away.
Radio signal's dead.

1232
01:26:35,000 --> 01:26:38,754
l'm flipping the backup generator.
Radio signal's gonna be cut in half
till we get main power back.

1233
01:26:38,880 --> 01:26:44,159
We're in segment 202, lateral grid 9,
site 15H-32, give or take a few yards.

1234
01:26:44,280 --> 01:26:47,397
Captain America here
blew the landing by 26 miles.

1235
01:26:47,520 --> 01:26:51,559
- How the hell do you know that?
- Because l'm a genius.

1236
01:26:51,680 --> 01:26:55,116
The gauges will not read.
They're all peaked, like we're
plugged into some magnetic field.

1237
01:26:55,240 --> 01:26:57,913
- Well, who on this spaceship
wants to know why?
- By all means.

1238
01:26:58,000 --> 01:27:00,878
The reason we were shooting for grid 8
was because thermographics indicated...

1239
01:27:01,000 --> 01:27:03,150
that grid 9
was compressed iron ferrite.

1240
01:27:04,520 --> 01:27:07,273
Which means you landed us
on a goddam iron plate.

1241
01:27:11,120 --> 01:27:13,918
All right. Well, you heard the man.
Let's wheel out the remote satellite
link. We need that radio.

1242
01:27:14,040 --> 01:27:16,918
Oh, God, please tell me
we still got one of 'em.

1243
01:27:18,600 --> 01:27:21,068
lndependence has flat-lined.

1244
01:28:03,240 --> 01:28:05,151
Oscar! Oscar!

1245
01:28:07,880 --> 01:28:10,155
Oh, God!

1246
01:28:12,680 --> 01:28:14,557
Hello! Anyone!

1247
01:28:14,640 --> 01:28:19,031
ls anyone else alive?
Somebody help me!

1248
01:28:20,960 --> 01:28:23,428
A.J.!

1249
01:28:23,560 --> 01:28:26,632
- Where are you?
- l'm here.

1250
01:28:30,880 --> 01:28:35,112
Lev, there's no one else.
There's no one else.

1251
01:28:35,240 --> 01:28:38,994
- l know.
- Oh, man.

1252
01:28:39,080 --> 01:28:41,913
- Bear, where are you?
- A.J.! A.J.!

1253
01:28:43,480 --> 01:28:46,392
l'm in the shuttle, man.

1254
01:28:46,520 --> 01:28:48,556
Are you all right?

1255
01:28:48,680 --> 01:28:50,875
l'm so glad to see you, man.

1256
01:28:51,000 --> 01:28:54,072
l never thought l'd be so happy
to see your ugly face.

1257
01:28:54,280 --> 01:28:57,750
- Houston, do you read? This is Freedom.
- Check your thrusters.

1258
01:28:57,880 --> 01:29:01,953
- Houston, do you copy?
- ls everyone good to go?

1259
01:29:11,560 --> 01:29:13,357
Wow.

1260
01:29:22,960 --> 01:29:26,270
Down here! ln the valley!

1261
01:29:26,400 --> 01:29:28,960
This place is like
Dr Seuss's worst nightmare.

1262
01:29:29,080 --> 01:29:33,790
Let's get the remote satellite.
We'll get better reception up there.

1263
01:29:33,920 --> 01:29:38,550
Bring Max down.
Watch yourself through here, Max.
There's a couple big fissures.

1264
01:29:38,680 --> 01:29:41,274
To the left!
Bring it to the left!

1265
01:29:46,760 --> 01:29:51,038
Rockhound, you come on down here
and take some readings
down in the flat spot.

1266
01:29:52,960 --> 01:29:54,837
lron ferrite.

1267
01:29:57,280 --> 01:30:01,558
- l have fire.
- Watts, l'm comin' back. Stand by.

1268
01:30:01,640 --> 01:30:05,428
- Mostly iron, Rockhound.
- God, l hate knowing everything.

1269
01:30:05,560 --> 01:30:08,358
We couldn't have picked
a worse spot to drill.

1270
01:30:08,480 --> 01:30:12,393
Well, l can pretty much guarantee
it's not gonna be thicker than 50 feet.

1271
01:30:12,520 --> 01:30:15,193
- How do you figure that?
- 'Cause if it is, we're screwed.

1272
01:30:17,480 --> 01:30:19,948
- Max, you good?
- Yeah. Just makin' hole.

1273
01:30:20,040 --> 01:30:23,077
- Turn it around.
- Friggin' outer space.

1274
01:30:25,960 --> 01:30:28,315
lt's good.

1275
01:30:33,800 --> 01:30:37,270
All right. We're in.
Bring another light.
We're cuttin' through pretty good.

1276
01:30:37,360 --> 01:30:40,636
There's some stuff in here
l ain't never seen.

1277
01:30:40,720 --> 01:30:44,156
All right, let's punch it down!

1278
01:30:44,280 --> 01:30:47,078
- Hey, Harry, did you see that?
- Yeah, Max, l see it. l see it.
What is it?

1279
01:30:47,200 --> 01:30:50,397
- We lost the bite in the bit.
- All right. Back it off. Back it off.

1280
01:30:50,520 --> 01:30:53,990
- Goddam it!
- Sounds like we twisted a shank.
Back it out of there, Max.

1281
01:30:54,120 --> 01:30:55,997
Good. Good. Hold 'er there.

1282
01:31:00,200 --> 01:31:02,873
Wow, this is
a goddam Greek tragedy.

1283
01:31:02,960 --> 01:31:06,873
- We've all seen
broken drill heads before.
- Not after ten feet.

1284
01:31:06,960 --> 01:31:09,793
- l never seen one.
- Well, now you've seen one.

1285
01:31:09,920 --> 01:31:12,195
- What do you want?
- Unpack the Judge.

1286
01:31:14,800 --> 01:31:17,109
Bear, Lev.

1287
01:31:17,200 --> 01:31:20,636
We're only three
astronauts left now.

1288
01:31:20,760 --> 01:31:24,309
We're not astronauts.
We're oil drillers.
We're not even supposed to be here.

1289
01:31:24,400 --> 01:31:26,755
What? You're not astronaut?

1290
01:31:26,880 --> 01:31:29,075
l'm getting us outta here. Get in.

1291
01:31:29,160 --> 01:31:32,118
- Why?
- Just get in the Armadillo.
l have an idea.

1292
01:31:32,200 --> 01:31:36,398
Houston, this is Freedom. Do you copy?
Houston, do you copy?
Freedom shuttle has--

1293
01:31:38,640 --> 01:31:40,949
We're gettin' some scattered video feeds
here so we're gonna have to lead over.

1294
01:31:41,040 --> 01:31:43,600
Houston, this is Freedom.
Do you copy?

1295
01:31:43,720 --> 01:31:46,871
- Thank God we have you, Freedom.
- Freedom, this is Houston. Go ahead.
- Don't lose 'em, Malloy.

1296
01:31:47,000 --> 01:31:50,231
Sir, we're getting something. Houston,
this is Freedom. We have landed safely.

1297
01:31:50,360 --> 01:31:53,557
- We are at site coordinates
approximately 15H-32--
- Where are they?

1298
01:31:53,640 --> 01:31:56,473
- Okay, l want to know everything
we can about that location.
- Got it.
- Get it before we lose 'em.

1299
01:31:56,560 --> 01:31:59,996
- We're also having electric
and antenna difficulties.
- Walter, get Mechanical on that.

1300
01:32:00,120 --> 01:32:03,715
- But we have commenced drilling.
- Stevens, we're losin' him.
Bring it up on four.

1301
01:32:03,840 --> 01:32:07,435
- Come on.
- On four.
- Shuttle flight capability
not yet known.

1302
01:32:07,560 --> 01:32:09,755
- Bump the signal.
- Bumping.
- Houston. Houston.

1303
01:32:09,840 --> 01:32:12,229
We lost 'em. Get 'em back.
Gruber, we need that hook-up.

1304
01:32:14,760 --> 01:32:17,558
l'll show you how we do things
where l come from.

1305
01:32:24,560 --> 01:32:27,358
Hold on!

1306
01:32:35,320 --> 01:32:37,231
Seat it.

1307
01:32:37,320 --> 01:32:39,515
All right, get ready.
Max, thread it.

1308
01:32:41,160 --> 01:32:44,118
Guys, the clock is tickin'.
Let's go, go, go, go, go!

1309
01:32:44,200 --> 01:32:46,475
All right! Good!
Crank it loose!

1310
01:32:46,600 --> 01:32:49,398
Keep it at 25. Let's kick
a little asteroid butt!

1311
01:32:49,480 --> 01:32:52,870
All right, Chick. Give me
more torque on the turbine, huh?

1312
01:32:53,000 --> 01:32:55,036
- Max, l need some more power down here!
- All right, boss.

1313
01:32:55,120 --> 01:32:58,192
-Throw it forward, then drop the hammer.
-Let's drill through this turd.

1314
01:32:58,280 --> 01:33:00,919
Come on, boys. We gotta hop.
We're fallin' behind.

1315
01:33:01,000 --> 01:33:03,833
Dig, dig, dig.
Chew this iron bitch up.

1316
01:33:08,520 --> 01:33:10,397
- Chick, the tranny is stuck.
- Harry!

1317
01:33:10,480 --> 01:33:13,392
- What is it?
- Chick, come on! Help!

1318
01:33:13,480 --> 01:33:15,311
- Release the clutch!
- Pull it up!

1319
01:33:15,400 --> 01:33:18,358
Okay. Well, this thing's
not movin'.

1320
01:33:18,440 --> 01:33:20,954
No, no, no!
Shut it down! Shut it--

1321
01:33:28,000 --> 01:33:30,036
This is not workin' out, Harry.

1322
01:33:30,120 --> 01:33:35,194
- Oh, are you all right?
- Oh, blew the tranny. Blew the tranny.

1323
01:33:35,320 --> 01:33:37,959
Come on, God.

1324
01:33:38,080 --> 01:33:41,629
Just a little help.
That's all l'm askin'.

1325
01:33:41,760 --> 01:33:44,957
l think we're close enough.
He might've heard ya.

1326
01:33:47,160 --> 01:33:49,833
Here's the bad news.
Before the asteroid passed the moon...

1327
01:33:49,960 --> 01:33:52,997
her rotation was stable
at 32 degrees on an X axis.

1328
01:33:53,120 --> 01:33:57,113
But now look at this.
The lunar gravity's put her in a spin.

1329
01:33:57,200 --> 01:34:00,510
She's tumbling on all three axes.
This wasn't expected, sir.

1330
01:34:00,640 --> 01:34:02,995
- What does this do for communications?
- Not good.

1331
01:34:03,080 --> 01:34:07,232
We'll have definite contact with the
shuttle for only seven more minutes.
After that, it's radio darkness.

1332
01:34:07,360 --> 01:34:12,309
- For how long?
- And after seven minutes,
we may never hear from them again.

1333
01:34:12,440 --> 01:34:16,149
But we're trying to bounce a signal off
a Russian military satellite,
reestablish contact that way.

1334
01:34:16,240 --> 01:34:20,438
lf we lose the shuttle com,
when do we lose the ability
to remote detonate that nuke?

1335
01:34:20,520 --> 01:34:22,988
The weapon remote receives
a signal from a Milstar satellite.

1336
01:34:23,080 --> 01:34:25,116
Higher orbit,
more powerful transmitter.

1337
01:34:25,240 --> 01:34:29,233
lf we've got the shuttle
for seven minutes, we can remote
detonate for an additional five.

1338
01:34:29,320 --> 01:34:32,471
What he's trying to say, General,
is that, uh, in 12 minutes' time
you may lose the ability...

1339
01:34:32,560 --> 01:34:34,994
to detonate the nuke permanently.

1340
01:34:35,080 --> 01:34:36,957
l've got to inform
the president.

1341
01:34:38,440 --> 01:34:42,115
Just want to make sure you know
we're stuck on an asteroid.
Do you know what you're doing now?

1342
01:34:42,240 --> 01:34:45,915
No, no. You know what? l have no idea
what l'm doing. l have no idea.

1343
01:34:46,040 --> 01:34:48,315
This button-- l don't know
what that does, okay?

1344
01:34:48,440 --> 01:34:53,594
All l know is that we just crashed
back there, l lost two of my friends,
we're 25 miles from Harry's shuttle.

1345
01:34:53,680 --> 01:34:56,114
We don't know if he's alive.
We don't know if he can fly.

1346
01:34:56,200 --> 01:35:00,432
All l know is there's a beep on this
thing and l'm trying to get us there.

1347
01:35:07,240 --> 01:35:10,357
Let's get it unpacked.

1348
01:35:10,440 --> 01:35:13,955
- What's up?
- We're drilling through some kind
of metal l've never seen before.

1349
01:35:14,080 --> 01:35:16,992
lt's fried two of our drill bits,
and now we blew our first transmission.

1350
01:35:17,120 --> 01:35:19,918
- So how deep are we?
- We could use your help
with the transmission, Colonel.

1351
01:35:20,040 --> 01:35:24,352
l have an assessment report due now.
We're supposed to be at 200 feet.
So how deep are we?

1352
01:35:24,480 --> 01:35:28,029
Not as deep as we'll be when
you quit askin' me all these questions
and help us load this transmission on.

1353
01:35:28,160 --> 01:35:31,357
- What is our current depth?
- Our current depth
is not important, Colonel.

1354
01:35:31,480 --> 01:35:36,793
l'll decide what's important.
We've got 800 feet to drill. You've had
two and a half hours. Where are we?

1355
01:35:39,040 --> 01:35:44,478
We're at 57 feet. Now,
if you're not too busy, maybe you can
give us a hand with this transmission.

1356
01:35:44,600 --> 01:35:49,594
Colonel Sharp! Get this wrapped up.
l'll be right back. Colonel Sharp!

1357
01:35:49,680 --> 01:35:52,831
All right. l'm coming through.
We have contact. Over.

1358
01:35:52,960 --> 01:35:57,795
- That's as clear as it's gonna get.
- Houston, this is Freedom. Do you copy?

1359
01:35:57,920 --> 01:36:01,879
Working at a remote satellite link
at this moment. Transmission change.

1360
01:36:01,960 --> 01:36:04,474
- Colonel!
- Twenty minutes.
Puts drilling final at ten hours.

1361
01:36:04,600 --> 01:36:08,195
Please advise. That's four hours past
the zero barrier. Please advise.

1362
01:36:08,320 --> 01:36:11,073
What the hell is this?
''Zero depth''?

1363
01:36:11,200 --> 01:36:13,668
And where'd this come from?
Who are you talkin' to? ls that Truman?

1364
01:36:13,800 --> 01:36:18,032
Let me have that phone.
Gimme the phone. Truman! Look,
this is what happens when you drill.

1365
01:36:18,120 --> 01:36:23,592
We cannot use your ''U.S. Air Force
Personnel Only'' drill time card.
Who wrote this thing, by the way?

1366
01:36:23,720 --> 01:36:27,076
- We're losing coms again.
- Look-- ls he getting this? Does he
hear me or-- What's wrong with this?

1367
01:36:27,200 --> 01:36:29,031
- The com's down.
- What do you mean, ''the com's down''?

1368
01:36:29,160 --> 01:36:33,756
- What do l mean? l mean we've
lost communication to mission control.
- Fine. Let's go back to the cargo bay
and get the transmission--

1369
01:36:33,880 --> 01:36:37,759
Hey, Harry, guess what.
You had your shot. You didn't do it.
You understand me? You can't--

1370
01:36:37,880 --> 01:36:42,476
Why don't you stay here and take you
and take your little drill card--
Write a report, why don't ya?

1371
01:36:42,600 --> 01:36:47,310
That'll be a-- My men and l
will go and get this hole dug!

1372
01:36:47,400 --> 01:36:51,029
You and your men are the biggest
mistake in the history of NASA.

1373
01:36:53,480 --> 01:36:56,153
- We've lost communication.
- Oh, God.

1374
01:36:58,760 --> 01:37:01,718
We're not lookin'
too good right now.

1375
01:37:01,800 --> 01:37:05,588
No shit.
We gotta get that radio back up.

1376
01:37:07,760 --> 01:37:10,718
Mr President,
it's time to make a decision.

1377
01:37:10,800 --> 01:37:15,032
We can remote detonate the bomb
for only another five minutes.

1378
01:37:16,840 --> 01:37:20,628
Yes? Kimsey here.
Yes, Mr President.

1379
01:37:20,760 --> 01:37:23,274
Yes, we saw that too, sir.

1380
01:37:23,400 --> 01:37:26,278
But maybe we should wait
until they--

1381
01:37:32,200 --> 01:37:36,955
Dan, get them out of there.
Evac right now.

1382
01:37:37,040 --> 01:37:40,032
- What's goin' on here?
- l've been ordered
to override the system.

1383
01:37:44,680 --> 01:37:46,955
Well, what is this?

1384
01:37:50,960 --> 01:37:53,474
Secondary protocol.

1385
01:37:58,560 --> 01:38:02,030
But they haven't drilled
the damn hole yet!

1386
01:38:05,280 --> 01:38:09,114
The president's advisors feel that
the drilling isn't working. And we've
lost radio contact, maybe for good.

1387
01:38:09,200 --> 01:38:12,476
We've only got a few minutes
left of guaranteed ability
to remote detonate that nuke.

1388
01:38:12,560 --> 01:38:14,915
lf we don't do it now we could lose
control, and we may never get it back.

1389
01:38:15,040 --> 01:38:17,759
Well, you tell the president that
he better fire his so-called advisors.

1390
01:38:17,880 --> 01:38:21,350
And if you detonate
that nuke on the surface,
we waste a perfectly good bomb...

1391
01:38:21,480 --> 01:38:24,278
and we have one chance
to save this planet!

1392
01:38:33,680 --> 01:38:35,636
l need that radio.

1393
01:38:35,720 --> 01:38:38,792
-Gruber, give me everything you got now!
-Roger that.

1394
01:38:42,280 --> 01:38:45,636
Yes, Mr President,
l understand that completely,
but my point is very, very simple.

1395
01:38:45,760 --> 01:38:48,513
And l think you need to trust me on
this because l know something about it.

1396
01:38:48,640 --> 01:38:51,154
l guarantee you, if you do this,
you kill us all.

1397
01:38:54,760 --> 01:38:56,830
Yes, sir.

1398
01:38:56,960 --> 01:38:59,190
General, he wants you.

1399
01:39:01,440 --> 01:39:04,512
This is Kimsey. Yes, sir.

1400
01:39:04,640 --> 01:39:06,551
l understand.

1401
01:39:08,600 --> 01:39:12,354
The orders are
to remote detonate in 30 seconds.

1402
01:39:12,480 --> 01:39:14,914
You have not told them yet!

1403
01:39:15,040 --> 01:39:17,349
That is my father up there!

1404
01:39:17,480 --> 01:39:20,631
- This is one order you shouldn't
follow, and you fucking know it!
- No! Don't touch me!

1405
01:39:20,760 --> 01:39:23,354
Let her go. Let her go!

1406
01:39:25,560 --> 01:39:28,120
Your key, sir.

1407
01:39:31,800 --> 01:39:34,439
God be with them.

1408
01:39:34,560 --> 01:39:37,472
Slow it down.

1409
01:39:42,320 --> 01:39:44,197
Harry...

1410
01:39:44,320 --> 01:39:48,029
the clock on that nine-foot
nuclear weapon is ticking.

1411
01:39:49,240 --> 01:39:53,631
Oh, my God! Sharp!
Get back here now!

1412
01:39:53,760 --> 01:39:55,796
Watts, get the shuttle
ready to evac now!

1413
01:39:55,880 --> 01:39:58,633
- lt just came on all by itself.
What-- What the hell's happening?
- Secondary protocol.

1414
01:39:58,760 --> 01:40:01,274
- What's that? What?
- Wait a minute.
- Secondary protocol.
- What does that mean?

1415
01:40:01,360 --> 01:40:03,669
- What the hell's secondary protocol?
- They're detonating this thing
from Earth.

1416
01:40:03,760 --> 01:40:05,637
- What do you mean, detonating? We
haven't even drilled the hole yet!
- We'll drop it in the hole.

1417
01:40:05,760 --> 01:40:09,230
- What're you talkin' about?
- The hole? Whoa, whoa!
- Get your helmets on now!
- Oh, no, no. How-How you turn it off?

1418
01:40:09,320 --> 01:40:13,279
- Colonel Sharp,
l got two men out on that rock!
- l got a man out there too.
We gotta evac now!

1419
01:40:13,360 --> 01:40:16,636
- Max, Rockhound, get back
to the shuttle, double-time!
- They could be on their way here.

1420
01:40:16,720 --> 01:40:20,679
They're not on their way here.
They would've talked to us by now.
We would've seen them.

1421
01:40:20,800 --> 01:40:23,792
- Watts, air lock the cockpit now!
- l copy you.

1422
01:40:23,880 --> 01:40:28,476
- Max, Rockhound!
- Hey, wait a minute!
How do you turn this thing off?
- Max, Rockhound--

1423
01:40:28,560 --> 01:40:30,391
- Harry, do you copy?
- Somethin's wrong.

1424
01:40:30,480 --> 01:40:35,110
- Yeah, it's all wrong, man.
We shouldn't even be up here.
- l know. Let's go back to the ship!

1425
01:40:36,400 --> 01:40:40,678
- l'm not leavin' without my men, Sharp.
- We've got two and a half minutes to
drop it and get off this rock.

1426
01:40:40,800 --> 01:40:43,155
lf they're not back by the time
we finish, we leave without 'em.

1427
01:40:43,240 --> 01:40:45,549
Okay, let's simplify this.
Let's just turn the bomb off right now.

1428
01:40:45,640 --> 01:40:48,200
lf we don't put this bomb down in
a hole 800 feet onto a fault line...

1429
01:40:48,320 --> 01:40:50,550
all you're gonna have
is a real expensive fireworks show.

1430
01:40:50,640 --> 01:40:53,074
This is turnin' into
a surrealistic nightmare here.

1431
01:40:53,160 --> 01:40:55,469
Watsler, are you listening?
lt's Truman.

1432
01:40:55,560 --> 01:40:59,348
Okay, listen to me carefully.
l want you to kill it. Kill the uplink.

1433
01:41:10,400 --> 01:41:13,597
- Give us the time, Sharp.
Shut this bomb down now!
- lt's not my call.

1434
01:41:13,680 --> 01:41:16,558
- Then whose call is it?
- Who made it?
- An order to detonate can only
come from the president.

1435
01:41:16,680 --> 01:41:18,750
- The president's not here!
You've gotta give us more time!
- Let's just turn it off now.

1436
01:41:18,880 --> 01:41:21,713
- l'm telling you
to shut this bomb down now!
- And l'm telling you it's not my call!

1437
01:41:21,800 --> 01:41:25,156
- Well, guess what.
l just made the call for you.
- Harry!

1438
01:41:27,240 --> 01:41:30,118
Don't. You could set it off.

1439
01:41:30,240 --> 01:41:33,710
Oh, man. What're you doin'
with a gun in space?

1440
01:41:36,640 --> 01:41:41,236
Come on. Come on. We gotta stop that
bomb right now. Kill the uplink.

1441
01:41:41,320 --> 01:41:46,394
- This thing is gonna blow.
We gotta get it off the ship.
- Easy.

1442
01:41:46,480 --> 01:41:51,634
- Stand down, Sergeant.
- Shut this bomb down and let us
finish our job the right way.

1443
01:41:51,720 --> 01:41:54,280
l'm under orders to protect
a surface detonation.

1444
01:41:54,400 --> 01:41:59,030
l'm gonna give you three seconds
to shut this bomb down,
and then l'm gonna make you shoot me.

1445
01:41:59,120 --> 01:42:01,953
Hurry, Watsler.
For Christ's sake, hurry.

1446
01:42:05,360 --> 01:42:07,351
What happened?

1447
01:42:11,040 --> 01:42:15,238
Sir, the override--
lt's been overridden.

1448
01:42:15,360 --> 01:42:19,353
l've bought us a couple
of minutes, so get that radio
workin', okay? Hurry, hurry!

1449
01:42:21,240 --> 01:42:25,597
Bring me all the way up here just to
blow me and my friends up? ls that it?

1450
01:42:25,720 --> 01:42:27,517
- Listen--
- Shut up!

1451
01:42:27,600 --> 01:42:31,149
Shut up, Colonel.
l'm talking now.

1452
01:42:31,240 --> 01:42:35,518
lt could start again.
lt might've been a warning.

1453
01:42:35,640 --> 01:42:38,598
- Uh-oh.
- That's why you are gonna
dismantle this bomb.

1454
01:42:38,720 --> 01:42:41,473
All right. What'd we miss?

1455
01:42:45,600 --> 01:42:48,876
- Do it again.
- Go.

1456
01:42:51,680 --> 01:42:53,398
Keep tryin'.

1457
01:42:54,760 --> 01:42:59,276
Sir, l need you to cease and desist.
l need your terminal now.

1458
01:43:02,000 --> 01:43:05,197
- Oh, they're reactivating the bomb.
- Comin' back on-line, sir.

1459
01:43:05,320 --> 01:43:07,993
Oh, geez. Here we go again.

1460
01:43:08,120 --> 01:43:11,237
What're you doin' up here? And why
did you even bother to make the trip?

1461
01:43:11,360 --> 01:43:14,113
To do the right thing,
to see that it's done.

1462
01:43:21,720 --> 01:43:24,359
For God's sakes,
think about what you're doin'.

1463
01:43:24,480 --> 01:43:27,790
Why are you listenin' to someone
that's 100,000 miles away?

1464
01:43:27,880 --> 01:43:31,350
We're here.
Nobody down there can help us.

1465
01:43:31,440 --> 01:43:34,910
So if we don't get this job done,
then everybody's gone.

1466
01:43:35,040 --> 01:43:37,474
One minute.

1467
01:43:37,600 --> 01:43:40,194
l've been drillin' holes
in the Earth for 30 years.

1468
01:43:40,320 --> 01:43:44,871
And l have never, never missed
a depth that l have aimed for.

1469
01:43:45,000 --> 01:43:48,037
And by God, l am not gonna miss
this one. l will make 800 feet.

1470
01:43:48,160 --> 01:43:51,152
42 seconds.

1471
01:43:51,240 --> 01:43:54,232
But l can't do it alone, Colonel.
l need your help.

1472
01:43:54,320 --> 01:43:57,596
You swear on your daughter's life,
on my family's...

1473
01:43:57,680 --> 01:44:00,194
that you can hit that mark?

1474
01:44:00,320 --> 01:44:04,233
l will make 800 feet.
l swear to God, l will.

1475
01:44:04,360 --> 01:44:07,193
Then let's turn this bomb off.

1476
01:44:18,080 --> 01:44:21,675
Steady. Steady.
Take it back. That's what you'll
have to do. Get 'em off backwards.

1477
01:44:21,800 --> 01:44:24,712
- Rainbow track? Under--
Under one? Under-- Okay.
- All of 'em. All of 'em. All of 'em!

1478
01:44:24,840 --> 01:44:28,435
- Okay. Okay. Are we free of static?
- Oh, do a good job. Do a good job.

1479
01:44:28,520 --> 01:44:32,149
- Steady. Steady.
- Good job. All right.
All right. All right.
- Go! Go! Go!

1480
01:44:32,280 --> 01:44:36,159
Red wire ''A.'' Ready? And-- Now.
Come on! Come on! Come on! Come on!

1481
01:44:37,400 --> 01:44:41,234
- Negative ''B.'' Ready, and now.
- Do a good job. Do a good job.

1482
01:44:41,320 --> 01:44:43,550
- Track flipped. Hots in.
- lt better be. Go.

1483
01:44:43,680 --> 01:44:45,398
Red or blue?

1484
01:44:47,160 --> 01:44:48,991
Wait--

1485
01:44:53,280 --> 01:44:55,669
Blue.

1486
01:44:57,640 --> 01:45:00,996
- Good job!
- You got it.

1487
01:45:03,680 --> 01:45:06,831
Oh, God, it sucks up here.

1488
01:45:06,920 --> 01:45:11,072
- Sir, the clock has stopped
at three seconds.
- What?

1489
01:45:11,280 --> 01:45:13,316
Have we lost
complete radio contact?

1490
01:45:13,400 --> 01:45:16,836
l got some magic happening.
We're bouncing off Russian and French
satellites. lt may have a faint signal.

1491
01:45:16,960 --> 01:45:19,599
Houston? Houston, do you copy?

1492
01:45:21,080 --> 01:45:23,310
Go ahead, Freedom.

1493
01:45:23,440 --> 01:45:26,398
Houston, you have a problem--
Problem.

1494
01:45:26,480 --> 01:45:30,268
See, l promised my little girl
that l'd be comin' home.

1495
01:45:30,360 --> 01:45:32,999
Now, l don't know what you
people are doin' down there...

1496
01:45:33,080 --> 01:45:35,833
but we got a hole
to dig up here.

1497
01:45:35,920 --> 01:45:38,639
Go, go, go, go! Come on.
We got work to do.

1498
01:45:38,760 --> 01:45:41,797
Okay, guys. All go, no quit.
How ya doin' down there? Good?

1499
01:45:41,920 --> 01:45:44,673
Okay, got the tranny.
We're back in business.

1500
01:45:44,760 --> 01:45:48,036
Hey, you guys should take a break
and come up and see this.

1501
01:45:49,680 --> 01:45:52,353
Wow. Got a great view
of the Earth from here.

1502
01:45:52,440 --> 01:45:54,590
Too bad we'll never
set foot on her again.

1503
01:45:54,680 --> 01:45:56,796
- Lev, do you see anything?
- No.

1504
01:45:56,880 --> 01:45:58,757
Well, keep goin'.
l'm not givin' up.

1505
01:45:59,920 --> 01:46:01,956
Hold up here, Bear.

1506
01:46:02,080 --> 01:46:04,116
- Oh, boy.
- This is great.

1507
01:46:04,240 --> 01:46:06,959
We just happen to run into
the Grand Canyon on the asteroid?

1508
01:46:07,080 --> 01:46:10,231
l told you, you took
a wrong way, a wrong road.

1509
01:46:10,320 --> 01:46:13,437
What-- What road? Do you see
any roads around here?

1510
01:46:13,520 --> 01:46:17,433
You know what? l do not have
much pleasure being near God's ear.

1511
01:46:17,520 --> 01:46:19,988
But you think this is
looking good, or what?

1512
01:46:20,080 --> 01:46:24,358
Lev, why don't you just do humanity
a favour and just shut the hell up?

1513
01:46:28,640 --> 01:46:30,915
Have you ever heard
of Evel Knievel?

1514
01:46:31,040 --> 01:46:33,270
No, l never saw Star Wars.

1515
01:46:39,280 --> 01:46:41,635
All right.
Doin' a good job.

1516
01:46:41,760 --> 01:46:44,069
- Give me a depth reading, Max.
- We're 150 feet, Harry.

1517
01:46:49,280 --> 01:46:52,829
Ride 'em, cowboy!
Yippee-kai-yo, kai-yay!

1518
01:46:52,920 --> 01:46:56,959
Get off the nuclear warhead.

1519
01:46:57,040 --> 01:46:58,951
l was doin' that guy
from that movie, you know...

1520
01:46:59,080 --> 01:47:02,038
Slim Pickens, where he rides it
all the way in-- the nuclear warhead.

1521
01:47:02,160 --> 01:47:04,833
- Now.
- Oh, you didn't see that one, huh?

1522
01:47:04,960 --> 01:47:07,713
We got 700 feet of hole
to dig, Rockhound.

1523
01:47:07,800 --> 01:47:11,634
All right. Just-- Just wanted to feel
the power between my legs, brother.

1524
01:47:12,840 --> 01:47:15,070
Hey, Sharp.

1525
01:47:15,160 --> 01:47:18,232
No nukes! No nukes!
No nukes!

1526
01:47:18,320 --> 01:47:20,231
You got any more bullets
in that gun, Sharp?

1527
01:47:20,440 --> 01:47:23,079
What did Watts tell you, Bear?
lf she kicked you in the balls,
you'd keep floating.

1528
01:47:23,200 --> 01:47:25,589
Yeah.

1529
01:47:26,640 --> 01:47:30,315
We turn the thrusters off, we jump
this thing, we float right over it.

1530
01:47:31,320 --> 01:47:32,992
Go over it again, Lev.

1531
01:47:33,120 --> 01:47:36,396
Throw the jet thrusters off
exactly when we jump.

1532
01:47:36,520 --> 01:47:40,035
- Okay.
- And then we're gonna put them on,
and we gonna go down nice and slow.

1533
01:47:40,160 --> 01:47:43,391
- That's it. That's it, baby. That's it.
- ls this gonna work?

1534
01:47:43,480 --> 01:47:47,519
- l don't know.
- Lev, you know what, just lie to me.

1535
01:47:47,600 --> 01:47:51,115
Let's say 50-50--
No. More like, uh--

1536
01:47:51,240 --> 01:47:53,276
like 70-30 or 80-20.

1537
01:47:53,360 --> 01:47:58,753
But you know what? lf it works, the two
of you gonna be heroes, just like me.

1538
01:47:58,840 --> 01:48:01,479
Screw it. We're jumpin'
over this canyon.

1539
01:48:05,400 --> 01:48:08,631
Just for the record,
this is a very bad idea!

1540
01:48:11,600 --> 01:48:15,639
- Wait for the edge now.
Wait till we get there. Wait--
- l'm waiting.

1541
01:48:15,760 --> 01:48:18,558
- Here we come. Now, not till we do it.
- Three...

1542
01:48:18,640 --> 01:48:20,949
- two, one!
- Here we go!

1543
01:48:21,080 --> 01:48:23,116
Off!

1544
01:48:30,520 --> 01:48:33,034
- Yes!
- lt's working!
- lt's working!

1545
01:48:33,160 --> 01:48:36,232
- Oh, my God!
- Yeah!

1546
01:48:36,360 --> 01:48:41,354
- l'm a genius! Wait a minute.
- Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

1547
01:48:41,480 --> 01:48:45,951
- We got some rocks!
- Go left! Go left!
- Lev! Lev, l can't do anything!

1548
01:48:46,080 --> 01:48:48,799
Turn!

1549
01:48:55,120 --> 01:48:57,953
Oh, okay, okay, we're
floating into outer space.

1550
01:48:58,080 --> 01:49:00,230
- Check main switch.
- Uh, this could be
a little bit of a problem.

1551
01:49:01,600 --> 01:49:03,670
- Thrusters on now!
- All right, turn 'em on.

1552
01:49:06,600 --> 01:49:11,720
- What's wrong?
- l-l don't know. The-The thrusters
not working. l hate this machine!

1553
01:49:11,800 --> 01:49:14,109
- l thought you had this planned!
What're we supposed to do?
- Be quiet! l must think!

1554
01:49:14,240 --> 01:49:17,152
- l'm stepping outside.
- You're-You're going outside?

1555
01:49:17,280 --> 01:49:22,593
l am the only certified astronaut,
and l'm saving your American ass!

1556
01:49:26,760 --> 01:49:28,512
Yes. You'll listen
to him. Right.

1557
01:49:33,520 --> 01:49:37,149
Hurry up, Lev, because we're
about a mile off the asteroid!

1558
01:49:37,240 --> 01:49:40,357
Just a second.
The fuel line is iced up.

1559
01:49:40,480 --> 01:49:44,678
- Yeah, l think maybe workin' now.
- No, Lev, it's not working!

1560
01:49:44,760 --> 01:49:47,513
l'm sorry, A.J.
l was way off the odds.

1561
01:49:47,600 --> 01:49:51,991
- We're gettin' higher, man.
- Look out! The rocks! Rocks are coming!

1562
01:49:58,640 --> 01:50:00,551
Hold on!

1563
01:50:04,280 --> 01:50:06,635
- Pull the thrusters!
- Lev, look out!

1564
01:50:13,200 --> 01:50:16,636
- We lost Lev.
- A.J.!

1565
01:50:16,720 --> 01:50:18,790
A.J., the thrusters!

1566
01:50:22,440 --> 01:50:24,476
Let's get Lev back!

1567
01:50:32,600 --> 01:50:34,909
Lev, hold on!
We're comin' in!

1568
01:50:50,840 --> 01:50:54,719
Thank You, Jesus. Thank You, Lord.
Thank You. Thank You,
thank You, thank You.

1569
01:50:57,240 --> 01:51:02,155
- Lev!
- Now l'm really a Russian hero!

1570
01:51:02,280 --> 01:51:05,397
- l told you!
- l know!
- l knew this would work!

1571
01:51:05,520 --> 01:51:08,796
-Good odds, you know?
-Come on, Lev. Get in here. We gotta go.

1572
01:51:13,720 --> 01:51:15,870
Rockhound, keep
on that transmission.

1573
01:51:16,000 --> 01:51:19,072
- Tranny looks good, Harry.
- All right. Take it outta there.

1574
01:51:19,160 --> 01:51:22,709
Lock it down, Chick.

1575
01:51:22,840 --> 01:51:25,274
Nice.

1576
01:51:25,400 --> 01:51:27,914
How come we didn't get
any training on this thing?

1577
01:51:28,040 --> 01:51:32,670
Whoa. Very cool. l could take out
this asteroid single-handedly.

1578
01:51:32,760 --> 01:51:34,955
Okay, boys, give it a rest.
l'll take it from here.

1579
01:51:36,080 --> 01:51:38,640
- Whoa!
- What the hell is that?

1580
01:51:38,760 --> 01:51:42,309
-lt's Rockhound.
-Whoa. This is so much fun, it's freaky.

1581
01:51:44,240 --> 01:51:46,276
Rockhound!

1582
01:51:46,360 --> 01:51:48,396
Whoa, watch your heads.
Sorry, Harry.

1583
01:51:50,880 --> 01:51:53,519
- Outta my way, boys!
- Rockhound!

1584
01:51:53,640 --> 01:51:56,029
Meet your maker, asteroid!

1585
01:52:00,320 --> 01:52:03,869
- What the hell's the matter
with you, Rockhound? Goddam!
- This is insane.

1586
01:52:03,960 --> 01:52:07,316
- Have you lost your mind?
- He's got space dementia.

1587
01:52:07,440 --> 01:52:09,510
Harry, you ought to
watch your man.

1588
01:52:11,960 --> 01:52:16,909
Max, downshift slowly
and put it in reverse.
We gotta get that pipe outta there.

1589
01:52:17,040 --> 01:52:19,110
Uh-oh.

1590
01:52:21,560 --> 01:52:24,279
- What's happening?
- The ground's cracking!
- Earthquake!

1591
01:52:32,280 --> 01:52:34,271
Quick, shut it off!

1592
01:52:35,600 --> 01:52:38,797
- Shut it off! Shut it off now!
- We're gonna have a blowout!

1593
01:52:38,920 --> 01:52:42,799
- We hit a gas pocket!
- We got pressure out the ass!

1594
01:52:43,480 --> 01:52:47,155
Max, get your helmet on!
Max, it's gonna blow!

1595
01:52:47,280 --> 01:52:50,238
- Oh, Jesus, l'm cooking!
- Max, get outta there!

1596
01:52:50,360 --> 01:52:52,920
This is it!

1597
01:52:53,040 --> 01:52:54,951
Harry!

1598
01:52:56,560 --> 01:52:58,471
l'm bailing!

1599
01:53:01,520 --> 01:53:02,953
Max!

1600
01:53:05,840 --> 01:53:08,434
- Goodbye, Max.
- Max!

1601
01:53:08,560 --> 01:53:11,438
- Take care, buddy.
- Armadillo's off the scope.

1602
01:53:11,560 --> 01:53:13,551
- l think we've had a blowout.
- No sign of the Armadillo.

1603
01:53:13,680 --> 01:53:15,750
Somebody punch up the Armadillo.

1604
01:53:43,960 --> 01:53:46,269
Get ahold of Truman.

1605
01:53:47,680 --> 01:53:50,319
Prepare the world
for bad news.

1606
01:53:57,000 --> 01:54:01,391
We're getting sketchy information
that the mission has suffered
massive failure.

1607
01:54:01,520 --> 01:54:05,274
And what we're trying to do
right now is to confirm that
and find out exactly what that means.

1608
01:54:05,400 --> 01:54:08,198
Repeat: We're getting leaks
from several NASA officials...

1609
01:54:08,280 --> 01:54:13,195
some rushing home
to be with their families,
that the drilling was unsuccessful.

1610
01:54:22,160 --> 01:54:24,754
This could very well be
our final hour.

1611
01:54:28,560 --> 01:54:30,357
We're gonna go
off the air now.

1612
01:54:30,480 --> 01:54:33,233
Good luck
and God bless.

1613
01:54:36,720 --> 01:54:38,392
- We've got incoming.
- l got tracks.

1614
01:54:38,520 --> 01:54:42,433
NORAD's tracking four small
incoming over Europe. They think
one's about to hit near Paris.

1615
01:55:07,880 --> 01:55:11,714
- Reports are coming in--
- Martial law has been implemented
in 42 countries.

1616
01:55:11,800 --> 01:55:14,109
Once the asteroid hits
zero barrier...

1617
01:55:14,200 --> 01:55:18,352
it will take about three hours
and 57 minutes to impact Earth.

1618
01:55:22,000 --> 01:55:25,993
Well, l guess we do it
the president's way. l'll order an evac.
You can remote detonate.

1619
01:55:26,120 --> 01:55:29,157
- You still don't think
this'll work, do you?
- Well, what l think is irrelevant.

1620
01:55:29,240 --> 01:55:32,073
- We need to do it now.
- Fine.

1621
01:55:32,160 --> 01:55:34,151
- Can they still take off?
- We hope so.

1622
01:55:34,280 --> 01:55:36,236
You are the one
that pulled them into this!

1623
01:55:36,360 --> 01:55:40,114
That is my family up there,
so l don't wanna hear, ''We hope so''!

1624
01:55:45,160 --> 01:55:48,914
Guess what, guys?
lt's time to embrace the horror.

1625
01:55:49,040 --> 01:55:52,510
Look. We got front-row tickets
to the end of the Earth.

1626
01:56:13,800 --> 01:56:17,270
- Yeah! Way to go, baby!
- Harry!

1627
01:56:22,600 --> 01:56:26,275
- Yeah!
- Yo, Harry! What's up, baby?

1628
01:56:26,360 --> 01:56:29,193
Hey, get that bomb outta there!
We got a hole to make!

1629
01:56:30,520 --> 01:56:32,636
Houston, you're not
gonna believe this...

1630
01:56:32,760 --> 01:56:35,228
but the other Armadillo
has arrived.

1631
01:56:35,320 --> 01:56:38,551
All right, people, listen up.
Settle down and focus.

1632
01:56:38,680 --> 01:56:41,990
- Mechanical, get on-line.
- P.P.O., gimme a set-up.
- Your boyfriend's back.

1633
01:56:43,440 --> 01:56:45,795
- Yo, Harry!
- You're awesome, baby!

1634
01:56:47,200 --> 01:56:48,872
Hey, Harry.
You miss me?

1635
01:56:49,000 --> 01:56:52,390
A.J., l got
just five words for ya.

1636
01:56:52,520 --> 01:56:55,671
- Damn glad to see ya, boy!
- That's six words.

1637
01:56:55,800 --> 01:56:59,110
- Chick, walk 'em down.
- So where's this hole you need dug?

1638
01:56:59,200 --> 01:57:01,430
Houston, drilling has recommenced.

1639
01:57:01,560 --> 01:57:06,918
- Do you think they can drill
250 feet in an hour?
- They better.

1640
01:57:07,000 --> 01:57:09,514
Bring that piece on in, Bear.

1641
01:57:09,640 --> 01:57:11,790
Tractor pull.

1642
01:57:11,920 --> 01:57:15,435
- l'm comin' down!
- We got 250 feet to go.

1643
01:57:15,560 --> 01:57:18,472
lt's our last transmission,
last drill head.

1644
01:57:18,600 --> 01:57:22,434
Punch it through.
First gear. We got contact.

1645
01:57:22,520 --> 01:57:25,990
Drive it on down, A.J.

1646
01:57:26,120 --> 01:57:28,918
- l got this, man. Let's go!
- Lev, the right engine hub.

1647
01:57:29,040 --> 01:57:33,192
- Houston, l'm getting no response
from the preflight sequence.
- Come on now. This is not--

1648
01:57:33,320 --> 01:57:37,632
Hey. Hey, come here. Can you get me
outta here, please, Lev? Thank you.

1649
01:57:38,720 --> 01:57:41,837
- Ow! Jesus! Hey!
- Wait. Uh, shh, shh.

1650
01:57:41,920 --> 01:57:44,229
- Lev, the right engine--
- Okay.
- Lemme outta here, will ya?

1651
01:57:44,360 --> 01:57:47,193
Just tryin' to have
some fun before l die!

1652
01:57:47,320 --> 01:57:50,756
- How deep are we?
- Seven seventy.

1653
01:57:55,880 --> 01:57:57,871
- Whoa, they got problems.
- The gauges are spiking.

1654
01:57:58,000 --> 01:57:59,956
Methane! Shut it down!
Back it down!

1655
01:58:00,080 --> 01:58:03,914
l can't pull back now. The bit'll
get lodged. We don't have enough time!

1656
01:58:04,040 --> 01:58:07,635
Whoa, whoa, whoa! lt's gonna blow!
lt's how we lost Max!

1657
01:58:07,760 --> 01:58:11,389
l know what l'm talkin' about.
We can punch through this.
We can knock this outta the park.

1658
01:58:11,480 --> 01:58:13,914
- This is our last transmission, A.J.
- Goddam it!

1659
01:58:14,040 --> 01:58:18,158
lf you're ever gonna trust me, ever,
once in your life, trust me now!

1660
01:58:18,240 --> 01:58:22,392
- Harry, it's gonna blow!
- Harry, l know what l'm doin'.
You just gotta trust me.

1661
01:58:24,480 --> 01:58:26,516
Make the call.

1662
01:58:28,280 --> 01:58:30,794
All right. Hold on.
l'm pushin' through her.

1663
01:58:36,200 --> 01:58:38,794
l'm pushin' through her!

1664
01:58:38,920 --> 01:58:41,718
- What's your depth?
- Seven seventy-five. Seven eighty.

1665
01:58:41,840 --> 01:58:45,196
Take it up, baby! Ram it home!

1666
01:58:45,320 --> 01:58:49,154
- Drive on down, A.J.!
- Seven eighty-five. Come on. Come on.

1667
01:58:49,240 --> 01:58:52,152
- Come on, A.J.!
- Punch it!
- Ninety-one. Come on.

1668
01:58:52,280 --> 01:58:55,272
Seven ninety-two.
Seven ninety-five!

1669
01:58:55,400 --> 01:58:57,868
Drive it down, A.J.!

1670
01:58:58,000 --> 01:59:00,389
Seven ninety-seven!
Ninety-nine!

1671
01:59:00,480 --> 01:59:03,597
- Breakthrough!
- Eight hundred! 802, Harry!

1672
01:59:03,720 --> 01:59:07,269
- Yeah!
- We did it!
- Harry, we did it!

1673
01:59:07,400 --> 01:59:08,879
- Yes!
- We did it!

1674
01:59:09,000 --> 01:59:12,913
- Yeah! Kid, way to go!
- l knew it, baby!

1675
01:59:13,040 --> 01:59:16,749
- lt's not over till we get
the bomb down that hole.
- Watts, they've got 38 minutes.

1676
01:59:36,760 --> 01:59:41,231
- Harry, you've gotta give me that hole.
- l'm gonna need two more minutes.
l got a bent pipe jammed in the hole.

1677
01:59:41,360 --> 01:59:44,955
We gotta cut it out before we can
send that bomb down. A.J.!

1678
01:59:45,080 --> 01:59:47,753
- She good to go?
- Yeah, l'm all set.
- All right.

1679
01:59:53,600 --> 01:59:56,034
- All right.
- A.J., come on! Make it fast!

1680
01:59:56,120 --> 01:59:59,271
l'm goin' as fast as l can!
There's a lot of gas pressure!

1681
02:00:05,640 --> 02:00:08,791
- You feel that?
- Harry, you gotta give me that hole.
The bomb is almost ready.

1682
02:00:08,920 --> 02:00:12,595
- Pull that pipe out!
- Harry, l'm almost through!
Give me 15 more seconds!

1683
02:00:18,280 --> 02:00:20,840
Well, this is somethin' new.

1684
02:00:22,880 --> 02:00:26,668
- l don't think this thing likes us.
- That's 'cause it knows
we're here to kill it.

1685
02:00:31,880 --> 02:00:34,314
Hey, what's goin' on
up there?

1686
02:00:38,080 --> 02:00:41,868
- A.J.!
- What the hell was that?

1687
02:00:42,000 --> 02:00:44,912
- A.J.!
- Goddam it, l'm finished!

1688
02:00:46,520 --> 02:00:49,034
- A.J., you all right?
- Oh, lot of gas pressure in here, man!

1689
02:00:49,120 --> 02:00:51,793
- Get me out!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Hydrogen pocket!

1690
02:01:09,480 --> 02:01:11,516
Harry! Pull me in!

1691
02:01:15,920 --> 02:01:18,036
A.J., hang on!

1692
02:01:22,560 --> 02:01:25,120
Secure the bomb!

1693
02:01:25,240 --> 02:01:27,879
Sharp, heads up!

1694
02:01:27,960 --> 02:01:29,951
Gruber! Get outta there now!

1695
02:01:31,520 --> 02:01:33,192
Oh, no.

1696
02:01:40,920 --> 02:01:42,797
Oh, God, no!

1697
02:01:47,960 --> 02:01:50,428
Look out!

1698
02:01:52,880 --> 02:01:56,236
Help! Oh, no!

1699
02:02:03,360 --> 02:02:05,715
Do you believe
that just happened?

1700
02:02:08,400 --> 02:02:10,960
- Sharp, you all right?
- l'm okay.

1701
02:02:11,040 --> 02:02:13,110
- Bear?
- Yeah. l'm here, Harry.

1702
02:02:13,240 --> 02:02:15,595
- A.J.?
- Yeah, l'm okay.

1703
02:02:18,160 --> 02:02:20,071
We lost Gruber.

1704
02:02:21,240 --> 02:02:25,199
- Gruber's dead.
- Let's get that bomb ready and go home.

1705
02:02:32,880 --> 02:02:35,110
Oh, my God.

1706
02:02:35,240 --> 02:02:39,313
- ls there a problem, Colonel?
- The timer, the remote,
the whole thing's dead.

1707
02:02:39,440 --> 02:02:41,396
What, the bomb is dead?

1708
02:02:41,520 --> 02:02:45,877
No, the trigger's dead. lt must've
gotten damaged during the rock storm.

1709
02:02:47,840 --> 02:02:50,354
So how do we detonate it?

1710
02:02:59,080 --> 02:03:03,756
We have 18 minutes to zero barrier.
We got some bad news.

1711
02:03:03,880 --> 02:03:06,872
The remote detonator on the bomb
has been damaged.

1712
02:03:07,000 --> 02:03:09,719
That means that somebody's
gonna have to stay behind.

1713
02:03:12,240 --> 02:03:14,435
lt takes two people
to fly this thing.

1714
02:03:14,520 --> 02:03:19,275
Either we all stay and die,
or you guys draw straws.

1715
02:03:19,360 --> 02:03:22,909
l say we all stay and die.
But that's me.

1716
02:03:23,960 --> 02:03:27,316
l'll draw. Let's draw.

1717
02:03:28,200 --> 02:03:30,668
Nobody's gonna draw straws.

1718
02:03:30,800 --> 02:03:33,394
- l'll stay and take care of it.
- Well, l can't live
with that sort of thing.

1719
02:03:33,520 --> 02:03:35,397
- Nobody asked you if you could
live with it, all right?
- Bullshit!

1720
02:03:35,480 --> 02:03:37,994
No way l will let you
volunteer for this...

1721
02:03:38,080 --> 02:03:41,629
so l can go back to my home country
like the man who didn't volunteer.

1722
02:03:41,720 --> 02:03:43,551
No way!

1723
02:03:43,640 --> 02:03:47,758
Hey, man, let's draw, and let's see
who's gonna stay up here and dance.

1724
02:03:47,880 --> 02:03:50,519
Guys, l-l-l know you guys
think l'm crazy right now...

1725
02:03:50,640 --> 02:03:54,235
but l would really like
this responsibility.

1726
02:03:54,360 --> 02:03:56,920
All right. All right.

1727
02:03:57,040 --> 02:03:59,110
- l can do it.
- Let's just draw straws and
get it over with. Come on.

1728
02:03:59,200 --> 02:04:01,031
l ain't drawin'
against you, Harry.

1729
02:04:01,120 --> 02:04:05,352
Well, l'm gonna draw against you, Chick,
so you better just go ahead and do it.

1730
02:04:05,480 --> 02:04:07,596
Just gimme this thing.

1731
02:04:14,120 --> 02:04:16,554
ls this good or bad?

1732
02:04:21,480 --> 02:04:24,995
Oh, man.

1733
02:04:25,080 --> 02:04:27,719
Well, we all gotta die, right?

1734
02:04:30,960 --> 02:04:33,793
l'm the guy who gets
to do it saving the world.

1735
02:04:33,880 --> 02:04:37,156
So, uh, let's go. We-We got
about ten minutes, right?

1736
02:04:38,960 --> 02:04:40,837
You plug this into the port.

1737
02:04:40,920 --> 02:04:45,311
Lift, press, hold. That's it.

1738
02:04:45,400 --> 02:04:49,313
Lift, press, hold. Shouldn't be
too tough. Even l can't screw this up.

1739
02:04:49,400 --> 02:04:51,914
l'll take him down.

1740
02:05:25,480 --> 02:05:30,156
Do me a favour, will ya?
Just tell Grace that, uh--

1741
02:05:30,280 --> 02:05:32,874
that l'll always be
with her, okay?

1742
02:05:35,000 --> 02:05:36,831
Can you do that?

1743
02:05:38,360 --> 02:05:40,396
Yeah. Okay, kid.

1744
02:05:46,200 --> 02:05:48,191
Give this to Truman.

1745
02:05:48,280 --> 02:05:52,239
Make sure Truman gets that.
Get in there.

1746
02:05:57,040 --> 02:05:59,110
lt's my turn now.

1747
02:06:00,360 --> 02:06:02,555
Harry! Harry!

1748
02:06:02,680 --> 02:06:06,036
You can't do this to me!

1749
02:06:06,160 --> 02:06:08,037
lt's my job!

1750
02:06:08,120 --> 02:06:12,079
You go take care of my little girl now.
That's your job.

1751
02:06:15,040 --> 02:06:18,032
Always thought of you
as a son. Always.

1752
02:06:19,600 --> 02:06:23,639
But l'd be damn proud
to have you marry Grace.

1753
02:06:23,760 --> 02:06:26,274
- Harry.
- You take care of yourself.

1754
02:06:26,360 --> 02:06:28,271
- Harry, no!
- l love you, pal.

1755
02:06:28,400 --> 02:06:31,153
Harry, l love you!
Don't, Harry! Wait a minute!

1756
02:06:31,280 --> 02:06:33,669
- My son.
- No, don't do this, Harry!

1757
02:06:33,800 --> 02:06:36,234
You don't do this! Harry!

1758
02:06:44,280 --> 02:06:46,430
What happened?

1759
02:06:46,520 --> 02:06:49,034
That crazy,
stubborn son of a--

1760
02:06:55,120 --> 02:06:58,556
Well, this was
a real good idea.

1761
02:06:58,680 --> 02:07:01,990
All right, let's go, Sharp.
Let's get our team outta here.

1762
02:07:06,720 --> 02:07:11,430
Come on! Let's get ready
to initiate thrusters! Let's go!

1763
02:07:11,560 --> 02:07:14,028
- l mean it, guys!
- Get the O2 masks.

1764
02:07:14,160 --> 02:07:16,720
- Are they free? Are they free?
- B.P.U., set.

1765
02:07:16,840 --> 02:07:20,196
l cannot believe this is going down
like this. You all right?

1766
02:07:20,280 --> 02:07:23,636
- O2 vents locked, pressure loaded.
- Engine board is green.

1767
02:07:26,040 --> 02:07:28,679
T minus three minutes
and counting.

1768
02:07:28,760 --> 02:07:31,274
Houston, do you copy?
This is Harry Stamper.

1769
02:07:32,600 --> 02:07:34,909
lt's down there.

1770
02:07:36,120 --> 02:07:40,750
- Electrical systems primed.
- B.P.U. is set. Oxidizers are loading.

1771
02:07:40,880 --> 02:07:45,032
Houston, we're outta here
in T minus three minutes.

1772
02:07:45,160 --> 02:07:47,230
Daddy?

1773
02:07:47,320 --> 02:07:50,278
Hi, Gracie. Hi, honey.

1774
02:07:50,360 --> 02:07:53,670
Grace, l know l promised you
l was comin' home.

1775
02:07:55,200 --> 02:07:57,031
l don't under-- understand.

1776
02:07:58,400 --> 02:08:01,517
Looks like l'm gonna have to
break that promise.

1777
02:08:03,760 --> 02:08:07,673
l, um--
l lied to you too...

1778
02:08:07,800 --> 02:08:10,360
when l told you that
l didn't want to be like you.

1779
02:08:12,280 --> 02:08:14,191
Because l am like you.

1780
02:08:14,320 --> 02:08:19,758
And everything good that l have
inside of me, l have from you.

1781
02:08:19,840 --> 02:08:22,354
l love you so much, Daddy.

1782
02:08:22,480 --> 02:08:25,119
l'm so proud of you.

1783
02:08:25,240 --> 02:08:27,356
l'm so scared.

1784
02:08:27,480 --> 02:08:29,516
l'm so scared.

1785
02:08:29,600 --> 02:08:34,435
l know it, baby, but there won't be
anything to be scared of soon.

1786
02:08:36,960 --> 02:08:42,159
Gracie, l want you to know
that A.J. saved us. He did.

1787
02:08:43,520 --> 02:08:45,476
l want you to tell Chick...

1788
02:08:45,560 --> 02:08:49,314
that l couldn't have done it
without him, none of it.

1789
02:08:50,840 --> 02:08:52,831
l want you
to take care of A.J.

1790
02:08:57,480 --> 02:09:00,119
l wish l could be there
to walk you down the aisle.

1791
02:09:03,320 --> 02:09:05,151
But l'll--

1792
02:09:07,560 --> 02:09:10,791
l'll look in on you from
time to time, okay, honey?

1793
02:09:13,120 --> 02:09:16,237
- l love you, Grace.
- l love you too.

1794
02:09:16,320 --> 02:09:18,959
- l gotta go now, honey.
- Daddy, no.

1795
02:09:20,200 --> 02:09:23,590
No, no, Dad, no!

1796
02:09:28,880 --> 02:09:32,350
O.M.S. pod pre-start.
O2 vents locked, pressure loaded.

1797
02:09:34,680 --> 02:09:36,716
What the hell's goin' on up there?
Why haven't you guys left yet?

1798
02:09:36,800 --> 02:09:39,439
We're going, Harry.
Houston.

1799
02:09:39,560 --> 02:09:41,994
- We got O.M.S. pod pre-start.
- Pod pre-start confirmed.

1800
02:09:45,720 --> 02:09:48,757
- What's the problem?
- l don't know.
- What's wrong?
- Fix it now!

1801
02:09:49,880 --> 02:09:51,871
No time, no time!

1802
02:09:51,960 --> 02:09:53,837
- What?
- What's that?

1803
02:09:57,520 --> 02:09:59,590
- Where you goin'?
- Oh, come on.
We're stayin', we're goin'.

1804
02:09:59,680 --> 02:10:01,511
We're stayin', we're goin'.
Make up your minds.

1805
02:10:01,600 --> 02:10:05,479
Damn it, Sharp! Get out of here now.
You got less than three minutes.

1806
02:10:08,640 --> 02:10:12,428
- Come on, Watts. Come on, come on.
- Blow the bomb, Harry. We're with you.

1807
02:10:12,560 --> 02:10:15,870
- Uh, it's stuck. Yes?
- Come on! Back off!
You don't know the components!

1808
02:10:15,960 --> 02:10:20,715
Components, American components,
Russian components. All made in Taiwan!

1809
02:10:20,800 --> 02:10:23,109
We're gettin' tight
for ignition, Freedom.

1810
02:10:26,040 --> 02:10:28,270
- Houston, we've got no fire.
- What does that mean?

1811
02:10:28,400 --> 02:10:31,915
- lt means we got a busted ship.
- A busted ship?
And l'm strapped in here?

1812
02:10:32,040 --> 02:10:34,031
l had a great spot
picked out there.

1813
02:10:34,160 --> 02:10:37,516
Freedom, you fire that engine.
lf there's not a way, you find
a way. The clock's tickin'.

1814
02:10:37,600 --> 02:10:39,909
Let's go! Let's fire
that engine, Freedom!

1815
02:10:40,040 --> 02:10:44,830
You got less than a minute.
Don't think l won't blow this thing.

1816
02:10:44,920 --> 02:10:47,434
Sharp, get out of here.
lt's gettin' bad down here.

1817
02:10:47,520 --> 02:10:49,511
l know how to fix it.
Please, move.

1818
02:10:49,640 --> 02:10:51,756
l-l have to take you away
if you don't move.

1819
02:10:51,880 --> 02:10:54,633
Watts, you gotta get that shuttle
started. You gotta fire it up now!

1820
02:10:54,720 --> 02:10:56,836
Damn it, Sharp.
Get off this rock!

1821
02:10:56,920 --> 02:11:00,230
l'm telling you, please, move!
This is how we fix problem...

1822
02:11:00,360 --> 02:11:03,397
in the Russian space station.

1823
02:11:03,480 --> 02:11:06,916
Because l don't want
to stay here any more.

1824
02:11:08,600 --> 02:11:12,434
Yeah! Finally!
We can go home!

1825
02:11:12,560 --> 02:11:14,790
- She's coming back. She's coming back.
- We're hot!

1826
02:11:14,880 --> 02:11:17,599
Watts, let's go, let's go!

1827
02:11:17,720 --> 02:11:20,757
Rain all you want,
you son of a bitch.

1828
02:11:20,880 --> 02:11:23,872
Let's go! We don't have time!
Hurry, hurry. We got no time!

1829
02:11:23,960 --> 02:11:27,589
lnitiate thrusters on my mark!
Two, one-- Mark!

1830
02:11:35,480 --> 02:11:38,916
- Come on. Get some altitude.
Let's go, let's go.
- Yes, come on!

1831
02:11:40,320 --> 02:11:42,436
Freedom has max thrust!

1832
02:11:48,880 --> 02:11:51,394
Thank you, Harry.

1833
02:12:01,000 --> 02:12:02,991
Shuttle's out of range.
Still no detonation.

1834
02:12:07,440 --> 02:12:10,352
Something's not right.
Too much time has gone by.

1835
02:12:11,920 --> 02:12:14,150
Zero barrier's about to be breached.
One minute.

1836
02:12:14,240 --> 02:12:16,708
Harry, come on.
Press that button.

1837
02:12:16,840 --> 02:12:20,833
- We're goin' back and do it ourselves.
- Just don't. Wait one minute.

1838
02:12:25,080 --> 02:12:27,799
- Dan, we're about
to cross the threshold.
- Come on, Harry. Press the button.

1839
02:12:27,920 --> 02:12:32,550
Colonel, l'm askin' you.
Just one more minute!

1840
02:12:38,560 --> 02:12:41,199
Press the button, Stamper.

1841
02:12:43,760 --> 02:12:46,194
Come on.

1842
02:12:47,680 --> 02:12:49,830
Harry'll do it. l know it.

1843
02:12:51,480 --> 02:12:54,040
He doesn't know how to fail.

1844
02:12:59,800 --> 02:13:01,472
We win, Gracie!

1845
02:13:03,080 --> 02:13:05,150
Press it!

1846
02:13:35,720 --> 02:13:38,951
We have detonation.
Confirming detonation.

1847
02:13:55,760 --> 02:13:58,149
The two halves are gonna miss us
by 400 miles...

1848
02:13:58,240 --> 02:14:01,516
and most of the small particles
have been vaporized.

1849
02:14:11,400 --> 02:14:14,198
- Houston, we're comin' home.
- We copy that, Freedom.

1850
02:14:14,320 --> 02:14:17,869
Yo, Harry. You the man.

1851
02:15:08,920 --> 02:15:12,390
Kennedy, we see you.
And you never looked so good.

1852
02:15:12,520 --> 02:15:17,878
l never told anybody
this before, but l hate flyin',
so it'd be an awful shame to die now.

1853
02:15:18,000 --> 02:15:22,039
That's easy for you to say. l owe
100 grand to a bad-ass loan shark...

1854
02:15:22,160 --> 02:15:24,674
which l spent on a stripper
named Molly Mounds.

1855
02:15:24,760 --> 02:15:27,752
- Boy, that's bad.
- Kennedy, we are 100%.

1856
02:15:27,840 --> 02:15:30,308
Flap suspension control on full.

1857
02:15:42,440 --> 02:15:44,749
Welcome home, astronauts.

1858
02:15:52,320 --> 02:15:54,436
Hey, guys, remember:
We're-- We're heroes now.

1859
02:15:54,520 --> 02:15:56,829
So that incident with me
and the gun on the asteroid--

1860
02:15:56,920 --> 02:15:59,275
Let's keep that under wraps,
all right?

1861
02:17:00,880 --> 02:17:02,757
Miss Stamper?

1862
02:17:04,080 --> 02:17:07,390
Colonel Willie Sharp,
United States Air Force, ma'am.

1863
02:17:07,480 --> 02:17:10,199
Requesting permission to shake
the hand of the daughter...

1864
02:17:10,320 --> 02:17:12,231
of the bravest man
l've ever met.

1865
02:17:18,560 --> 02:17:20,391
Hello.

1866
02:17:20,520 --> 02:17:22,954
- Oh, my God!
- Hi, you're my hero.

1867
02:17:23,080 --> 02:17:26,595
Oh, baby, l wanna have babies
with you.

1868
02:17:28,440 --> 02:17:30,271
Welcome back, cowboy.

1869
02:17:32,160 --> 02:17:36,199
Uh, Harry wanted you
to have this.

1870
02:17:42,480 --> 02:17:44,357
He did, huh?

1871
02:18:01,040 --> 02:18:03,315
l could stay awake

1872
02:18:03,440 --> 02:18:08,434
Just to hear you breathin'

1873
02:18:08,560 --> 02:18:12,155
Watch you smile while you are sleepin'

1874
02:18:12,280 --> 02:18:16,558
While you're far away and dreamin'

1875
02:18:16,640 --> 02:18:20,519
l just wanna stay with you

1876
02:18:20,600 --> 02:18:23,194
ln this moment forever

1877
02:18:23,320 --> 02:18:26,039
Forever and ever

1878
02:18:26,160 --> 02:18:29,675
l don't wanna close my eyes

1879
02:18:29,800 --> 02:18:32,234
l don't wanna fall asleep

1880
02:18:32,360 --> 02:18:34,271
'Cause l'd miss you, baby

1881
02:18:34,360 --> 02:18:37,352
And l don't wanna miss a thing

1882
02:18:37,440 --> 02:18:41,228
'Cause even when l dream of you

1883
02:18:41,360 --> 02:18:43,920
The sweetest dream would never do

1884
02:18:44,000 --> 02:18:45,831
l'd still miss you, baby

1885
02:18:45,920 --> 02:18:48,639
And l don't wanna miss a thing

1886
02:18:48,760 --> 02:18:52,673
And l don't wanna miss one smile

1887
02:18:52,760 --> 02:18:56,594
And l don't wanna miss one kiss

1888
02:18:56,720 --> 02:18:59,917
Well, l just wanna be
with you right here

1889
02:19:00,000 --> 02:19:03,913
With you just like this

1890
02:19:04,040 --> 02:19:07,999
Well, l just wanna hold you close

1891
02:19:08,120 --> 02:19:12,159
Feel your heart so close to mine

1892
02:19:12,280 --> 02:19:15,636
And just stay here in this moment

1893
02:19:15,760 --> 02:19:20,197
For all the rest of time

1894
02:19:20,280 --> 02:19:22,396
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah

1895
02:19:22,520 --> 02:19:25,318
Yeah

